  "bib_entries": {
    "121442005": {
      "title": "Intersecting random translates of invariant Cantor sets",
      "abstract": "Given two Cantor setsX andY in [0, 1), invariant under the mapx\u2192b x mod 1, the Hausdorff dimension of (X+t)\u2229Y is constant almost everywhere. WhenX,Y are defined by admissible digits in baseb, and more generally by sofic systems, we compute this dimension in terms of the largest Lyapunov exponent of a random product of matrices. The results are extended to higher dimensions and multiple intersections."
